1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,030
A Kafka cluster is a group of brokers — individual server processes, each with a unique integer ID.

2
00:00:05,980 --> 00:00:15,740
One broker is elected the Controller, responsible for administrative duties: partition leader elections, topic creation and deletion, and cluster metadata propagation.

3
00:00:15,740 --> 00:00:21,288
If the Controller broker dies, another is automatically elected , let that sink in for a second.

4
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:26,019
Most developers think more Topics and Partitions means better performance.

5
00:00:26,019 --> 00:00:28,538
It can , actually make things worse.

6
00:00:28,538 --> 00:00:30,288
Stay tuned to see why.

